<SLUG> BC-MAC-REPORT10-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    New Apple OS introduces Sherlock
 &HT;    By Bill Husted
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ OS 8.5, the latest version of the Apple Computer
operating system, represents another incremental step forward for
the Mac. By and large, OS 8.5 is a collection of small but
important tweaks.
</P>
<P>
   The one exception is a potentially important new technology
called Sherlock. It's a search engine that replaces the Mac's aging
Find application. But more on that later.
</P>
<P>
   While receiving good reviews overall, OS 8.5 has generated some
disturbing complaints. A few users have reported severe damage to
the data and programs on their hard drives. Others have complained
that, over time, the icons on their Macs have slowly disappeared
with OS 8.5.
</P>
<P>
   Most of these complaints have been linked to Mac clones or Macs
using drivers other than Apple's. Apple Computer has launched a
major investigation to identify and correct the problem.
</P>
<P>
   It's not unusual for a new version of the operating system to
cause problems. Most are corrected within a few months. So it
wouldn't be unwise to wait a bit before buying OS 8.5, which
retails for $99.
</P>
<P>
   Personally, I've been playing with OS 8.5 for about three weeks
and have experienced no problems. It has worked fine on both a G3
PowerBook and G3 desktop.
</P>
<P>
   By far OS 8.5's biggest innovation is Sherlock. It lets you
search for files through hard drives, networks and the Internet.
With the old Find application, you could only search through file
names and characteristics. In addition, Sherlock lets you search
the content of a file.
</P>
<P>
   For example, I launched a search for the word Michelangelo,
which was buried within one of the hundreds of files on my hard
drive. Sherlock found this file in a split second.
</P>
<P>
   Sherlock ranks its findings by relevance, a presentation that
mimics a style now common on the Net. Indeed, Sherlock looks and
acts more like a Web search engine.
</P>
<P>
   Sherlock also incorporates some long-awaited file management
improvements. Click on a listed file and you jump right to it. You
can also move files _ to another folder, the desktop or the trash _
by simply dragging them.
</P>
<P>
   Sherlock is only one of many new features in OS 8.5. I will
examine others, including small but helpful ones, in the weeks
ahead.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
