<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Titantic CD-ROM offers unreleased film footage
 &HT;    By Mark Clothier
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ If you're one of the millions who didn't see
``Titanic,'' the movie and didn't buy the video, the soundtrack or
the book, there's still at least one more chance to give money to
James Cameron this year.
</P>
<P>
   Fox Interactive is releasing James Cameron's Titanic Explorer, a
CD-ROM, at a suggested $35. It is billed as the only Titanic
multimedia product that blends a historical database with
previously unreleased film footage. Users will be able to tour the
ship and see what it looked like on its maiden voyage.
</P>
<P>
   The three-disc CD-ROM set uses original blueprints and
underwater footage from Cameron's own dive, and includes more than
800 historical photos. The CD-ROM lets you conduct keyword searches
on facts related to the Titanic, its crew, its passengers and
historical data.
</P>
<P>
   The CD-ROM set works on Macintosh or PCs. For PCs, it requires
at least a 166 megahertz processor, Windows 95 and 16 megabytes of
installed RAM, and 30 megabytes freed up on your hard drive.
</P>
<P>
   A PowerMac with at least a 7.6.1 operating system is required.
</P>
<P>
   Get debt relief
</P>
<P>
   If your budget has yet to wane from last year's holiday waxing
and you are worried about this year's impending shopping season,
there might be help online.
</P>
<P>
   Debt Relief is a single-user version of Debt Analyzer, a
software program available from Insight Software Solutions, at
http://www.debtanalyzer.com.
</P>
<P>
   The software does what a financial adviser does: It looks at
what you owe and figures out how you can pay it back as painlessly
and inexpensively as possible.
</P>
<P>
   Debt Analyzer lets the debtor choose the amount of monthly
payment. The software also lets you view your payments and balances
in graphic and statistic form.
</P>
<P>
   The software comes in three versions: ad-supported, which is
free; a standard version, which has no advertising and costs $10;
and the private label, which can be customized with a company logo.
</P>
<P>
   Debt Relief is a 32-bit program and is suited for Windows 95,
Windows 98 and Windows NT.
</P>
<P>
   The way to fly
</P>
<P>
   If you prefer the control and convenience of buying your airline
tickets online, there's a Web site that will let you do the same
thing with the insurance buying process.
</P>
<P>
   http://www.quotesmith.com has been up for two years. President
Bob Bland ran an online quote service for insurance agents and
brokers before that.
</P>
<P>
   The site is similar to an online travel agency, in that you can
take the information it provides to your broker or you can buy the
insurance online. The price is the same either way.
</P>
<P>
   Bland said he sells 1,800 policies on the site each month.
</P>
<P>
   The site offers individual family and medical insurance,
individual term life insurance, automobile insurance, final expense
whole life insurance, fixed annuities and Medicare supplement
insurance quotes from 375 companies.
</P>
<P>
   Bland recently added an auto insurance link with Progressive,
the fifth-largest auto insurer.
</P>
<P>
   Online bookstore
</P>
<P>
   MovieStreet, the company that runs KidFlix.com, an online family
video store, announced recently it is creating an online children's
bookstore.
</P>
<P>
   The online store will be located at the KidFlix.com Web site and
will open in mid-November.
</P>
<P>
   The bookstore will be called barnesandnoble at KidFlix.com. The
site will offer thousands of children's book titles, cross-linked
with children's videos. Barnesandnoble.com also will stage live
chats with children's authors at the site.
</P>
<P>
   KidFlix.com is an Internet seller of family-oriented videos.
MovieStreet, the company that owns KidFlix.com, is a marketing and
publishing company that develops electronic commerce businesses.
</P>
