   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ Elections are family reunions after a fashion,
and the obligatory snapshot from last week's catches the clan in
its usual disarray, complete with a scowling uncle or two, some
perky moms and a couple of kids blurry because they couldn't sit
still. (Isn't that Newty running off?) What the picture doesn't
show is the family forming up to go marching off on some great
political toot, eternally the hope in some of our more lurid
ideological precincts. Rather, it finds us, as usual, having things
a bit of both ways. (Teepen, Cox Newspapers)
</P>
