   WITH
</P>
<P>
   LEGOROBOT _ Oct 1 is the release date for Lego Mindstorm, a new
Lego product where you can build a robot from Lego pieces, program
it on your computer, and have the robot act out what you tell it to
do, thanks to a microprocessor embedded in the Lego robot. The toy
is $200; Lego is lending us one for a month. The premise of the
story is this: we get three engineers, give them each one of the
toys, and give them an afternoon to see what they come up with. we
take pictures and have a little graf showing what each robot does.
Tech geeks (of which there are plenty in Austin) fondly recall
playing with regular Lego pieces as children, and now that they're
grown up and working as computer engineers, they can't wait to play
with this robot version. (Santos, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
