<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Saturday, Nov. 7, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Tina May at (206) 448-8355.
</P>
<P>
   CLOUDS-WEATHER (Seattle) As a troubled youth on the streets of
postwar London, Peter Hobbs was taken aside by a member of the
British weather service and introduced to the wonders of clouds in
the hope that it might help curb his delinquent behavior. It did.
And Hobbs has kept his head in the clouds since.
</P>
<P>
   On Friday, Peter Hobbs, University of Washington atmospheric
scientist and director of the UW's world-renowned Cloud and Aerosol
Research Group, celebrated his team's latest achievement with the
dedication of a ``new'' research airplane at Paine Field in
Everett, north of Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   By Tom Paulson. (story will move in the ``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   TV-COLUMN-MCBEAL (Undated) On all the brouhaha surrounding
Calista Flockhart's thinness.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (story will move in the ``e'' category)
