<HEADLINE>
`HORSE WHISPERER' SCENIC `JAMES ELLROY' CRAZY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1998 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES:  &UR; ``The Horse Whisperer''  &LR; _ The big cineaste
question of the decade: Who gets more backlighting, Barbra
Streisand or Robert Redford? As if he were looking to market
postcards, Redford photographs beautifully against the magnificent
Big Sky country. But that's it. How are we supposed to care about a
spoiled rich kid and her taciturn mother, stonily played by Kristin
Scott Thomas? They didn't even get the horse stuff right. Just ask
the real horse whisperer, Monty Roberts.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``James Ellroy: Demon Dog of American Crime Fiction''  &LR; _ The
author of ``L.A. Confidential'' and dozens of other crime novels
takes us on a tour of low-life LA. Driving a big old American
convertible and wearing a flashy Hawaiian shirt, Ellroy bemoans the
changes in the Los Angeles landscape he grew up to hate and love
during the '50s. He even points out a pleasant home where he used
to peep in the window. Frankly, if ``Demon Dog'' is to be believed,
he seems as creepy and crazy as some of his characters.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Music From Another Room'' &LR;  _ Brenda Blethyn, Gretchen Moll,
Jennifer Tilly, and Jane Adams save this love story from falling
into a sentimental abyss. True love never runs smooth, but it's
seldom rockier than it is in this provocative, star-crossed tale.
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS:  &UR; Nov. 13:  &LR; ``Armageddon.''  &UR; Nov. 14 &LR; :
``Creaturealm Demon's Wake.''  &UR; Nov. 17:  &LR; ``Fear and Loathing in Las
Vegas,'' ``An All Dogs Christmas Carol,'' ``Photographing
Fairies,'' ``Letter From Death Row,'' ``Dirty Work,'' ``The Land
Girls,'' ``Can't Hardly Wait,'' ``Kristin Lavransdatter,''
``Armistead Maupin's More Tales of the City,'' ``High Art,'' ``Dead
Fire,'' ``My Husband's Secret Life,'' ``The Survivor,'' ``Passion
in the Desert.''  &UR; Nov. 24:  &LR; ``Dr. Dolittle,'' ``The Negotiator,''
``Addicted to Murder 2: Tainted Blood,'' ``Eden,'' ``Soldier of
Fortune,'' ``Phoenix,'' ``Bang,'' ``Angel Blue,'' ``Sliding
Doors.''  &UR; Nov. 27: &LR;  ``Deep in the Heart (of Texas).''  &UR; Dec. 1:
 &LR; ``The Mask of Zorro,'' ``Sliding Doors,'' ``Land Before Time VI,''
``Almost Heroes,'' ``The Last Seduction 2,'' ``The Robin Hood
Gang.''  &UR; Dec. 8:  &LR; ``The Parent Trap,'' ``Lured,'' ``Alibi,''
``Double Edge,'' ``Sour Grapes,'' ``Urban Safari,'' ``It Happened
Tomorrow.''  &UR; Dec. 15: &LR;  ``The Boxer,'' ``Madeline,'' ``How I Spent
My Summer Vacation,'' ``Half Baked,'' ``The Strauss Family,'' ``A
Friend of the Deceased,'' ``Indiscreet.''  &UR; Dec. 18:  &LR; ``Air Bud:
Golden Receiver,'' ``Summer of the Monkeys.''  &UR; Dec. 22:  &LR; ``Blade,''
``Baseketball,'' ``The Secret of Nimh 2,'' ``Billy's Hollywood
Screen Kiss,'' ``Random Encounter,'' ``Act of War.''  &UR; Jan. 5:
 &LR; ``Out of Sight,'' ``Every Mother's Fear,'' ``Scarred City.''
</P>
