 &HT;    
 By EVERETT POTTER 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
 &HT;    New Year's Eve, 1998? Think of it as practice.
 &HT;    Most serious party lovers already have their eyes on the bash of
the century, Dec. 31, 1999. Many of them have already made their
plans, and plenty of hotels have been booked for ages.
 &HT;    But for travelers who haven't decided what to do, here's a
selection of travel-related parties that should make it easy to
welcome in the millennium with a bang. Prices are based on
double-occupancy unless otherwise noted.
 &HT;    The Big Apple looms large for party-goers on the ultimate New
Year's Eve, and the Rhiga Royal Hotel (151 West 54th St., New York,
N.Y. 10019; 800-937-5454) has a deal for couples from Dec. 31 to
Jan. 2, 1999.
 &HT;    Chauffeur-driven limousine transportation brings guests to one
of the hotel's Grand Royal Penthouse suites that overlook Central
Park and the Hudson River.
 &HT;    On New Year's Eve, each couple is brought by limousine to the
Rainbow Room to ring in the millennium with a dinner dance. New
Year's Day starts with breakfast en-suite and continues with a
Broadway show of the couple's choice.
 &HT;    The final day brings brunch and the bill _ just $10,000 per
couple.
 &HT;    Down in the Caribbean, the Bitter End Yacht Club (North Sound,
Virgin Gorda, BVI; 800-872-2392) has cozy hillside and beachfront
villas, a sailing school and a recipe for a party.
 &HT;    The BEYC 2000 Celebration is a 10-day package that includes a
millennium bash with 15 different bands from Virgin Gorda playing a
12-hour session on New Year's Eve. The partying will take place on
shore and on boats, with a fireworks display at midnight.
 &HT;    The package includes accommodations, transfers, all meals,
beverages, use of boats, all entertainment and theme dinners. The
cost is $10,800 per couple, based on double occupancy.
 &HT;    Perhaps the tranquility of the English countryside beckons on
this special New Year's? The Lygon Arms (High Street, Broadway,
WR12 7DU, England; 800-63-SAVOY), located in the Cotswolds, has a
three-night package that will mark the millennium as well as its
own 500 year anniversary.
 &HT;    The millennium package at this Savoy Group hotel includes a
helicopter tour of the Cotswolds, a New Year's Eve ball and the
services of both a graphologist and a psychic on New Year's Day to
help everyone peer a little bit farther into the future.
 &HT;    Accommodations and most meals are included in the price, which
is $1,411 per person.
 &HT;    The Broadmoor (Box 1439, Colorado Springs, Colo. 80901;
800-634-7711) which dates from 1918, is one of the grandest hotels
in the West.
 &HT;    This Rocky Mountain treasure will have ``A Celebration of the
Centuries,'' an all-inclusive weekend party that offers activities
ranging from a dinner dance to a New Year's Eve show with
Bernadette Peters and the Temptations.
 &HT;    New Year's Day will feature Bloody Mary ``First Aid Stations.''
Such classic Colorado pleasures as horse-drawn sleigh-and-carriage
rides will be available during the quieter moments. The cost starts
at $2,500 per person.
 &HT;    Both Royal Caribbean International (1050 Caribbean Way, Miami,
Fla. 33132; 800-327-6700) and Celebrity Cruises (1050 Caribbean
Way, Miami, Fla. 33132; 800-437-3111) have announced ambitious
millennium plans for cruisers.
 &HT;    For example, Royal Caribbean's ``Voyager of the Seas,''
``Enchantment of the Seas,'' ``Grandeur of the Seas,'' ``Sovereign
of the Seas'' and Celebrity's ``Century'' will convene at midnight
on New Year's Eve off Coco Cay in the Bahamas for a fireworks
display in the midst of individual millennium itineraries. Contact
a travel agent or cruise-only agent for prices.
 &HT;    The Ritz-Carlton (3414 Peachtree Road N.E., Suite 300, Atlanta
Ga. 30326; 800-241-3333) has the Ultimate Experience. Reserved for
just one couple at each of the Ritz-Carlton hotels, the package
includes three nights in the Ritz Carlton Suite, the premier suite
in each hotel, which includes a private dining room and butler.
 &HT;    Men receive an 18-karat gold Bulgari Chronograph while ladies
receive an 18-karat gold Bulgari Quadrato.
 &HT;    The two lucky guests also receive a magnum of Taittinger
champagne, two Baccarat flutes, limousine transfers and a Jaguar at
their disposal all weekend. All meals and parties are included.
 &HT;    For example, conductor Peter Duchin will be on hand at the
Ritz-Carlton, Boston, while Lou Rawls will hold court at The
Ritz-Carlton, Naples (Fla.).
 &HT;    The price for the Ultimate Experience is $100,000 per couple.
For those who aren't prepared to part with that kind of change,
there are packages with three-night minimum stays that start at
$450 per room, per night. Contact Ritz-Carlton for a Millennium
Experience brochure.
 &HT;    Finally, for those who absolutely must be together with their
closest friends in New York City on New Year's Eve, the Fitzpatrick
Manhattan Hotel (687 Lexington Ave., New York, N.Y. 10022;
212-355-0100) is prepared.
 &HT;    This midtown New York hotel with an Irish flavor is offering one
enterprising celebrant and 181 of their closest friends the chance
to take over the entire 17-story hotel for three nights. That's 51
suites and 40 rooms, with a two- person limit per room.
 &HT;    All food, alcohol and entertainment are included, as are a New
York Harbor cruise with a Swing Band on board and a New Year's Eve
extravaganza with a Motown Band and a Medieval Banquet.
 &HT;    The cost? A cool $1 million. Well, it only happens once a
century.
 ---- 
 &HT;     (Everett Potter is a New York-based free-lance writer.)  
 &HT;     c.1998 Everett Potter  
