   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   IMPEACHMENT-DEFINITION (Washington) _ Legal scholars and
historians disagree in their testimony before a House Judiciary
panel trying to define what is an impeachable offense. But the
argument may turn into an academic exercise because of turmoil
within the GOP House leadership and the public mood against
impeachment. By DAN FREEDMAN.
</P>
<P>
   COURT-CLINTON (Washington) _ The Supreme Court rejects President
Clinton's appeals to let Secret Service agents and government
lawyers refuse to answer questions about possible criminal conduct
by Clinton and other government officials. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-LEADERSHIP (Washington) _ In the game of musical chairs
among House leaders, the race for the majority leader's seat
appears to pit incumbent Rep. Richard Armey of Texas against
challengers Steve Largent of Oklahoma, Jennifer Dunn of Washington
and Dennis Hastert of Illinois. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
