</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Trying to figure how to get out of
an impeachment process the voters don't want, House Republicans are
discovering an old military truism _ it is easier to start a war
than end one. Even so, Democrats have suffered a blow with the loss
of their most useful bogeyman, Newt Gingrich. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
<P>
   SWISS-JEWS (Paris) _ The recently settled controversy over how
much Swiss banks owe to the relatives of Jewish depositors later
killed by the Nazis has unleashed a strong wave of anti-Semitism in
Switzerland, according to a new government report. Among the most
interesting points is the admission that anti-Jewish sentiment
among the Swiss was already widespread before the dispute erupted.
By BERNARD D. KAPLAN.
</P>
