</P>
<P>
   NIXON-PRECEDENT (Washington) -- Although some Democrats at the
time wanted to impeach Richard Nixon for every possible crime, the
outcome generally supports current Democrats' view that impeachment
should deal only with issues that directly affect governance. By
Peter Canellos. 1900 words.
</P>
<P>
   GUNS-ELECTIONS (Washington) -- In the tightest races this year,
candidates painted their opponents as extremists for failing to
support gun control measures, and political observers say it
worked. At the polls, NRA forces took a beating, while gun-control
advocates scored big. By Louise D. Palmer. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   OLIPHANT-COLUMN (Washington) -- An exquisite irony is that the
leading forces to replace Newt Gingrich are directly in conflict
with the forces on his right he felt made his continued tenure
impossible. By Thomas Oliphant. (w and k coding)
</P>
